  "doc_id": "42707",
  "text": "Previous research has highlighted that many cancer patients in Iran may not know the exact diagnosis of their disease [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and only limited information is disclosed to cancer patients. Therefore, an important clinical concern in this study was to ascertain the participant's own awareness of their diagnosis of cancer. [CITATION_3] In order to ascertain this and prevent unwanted disclosure, this information was obtained from the patients caregivers and/or health care professionals and then checked with the patients via a short private interview. This procedure was approved by the local Ethics Committee. This study was approved by Regional Ethics Committee at TUOMS. All participants were informed of the study aims and objectives. Written consent was obtained.",
